<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-21T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-21T08:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">741.9411/33: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Davis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-21T14:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">May 21,
                                        1920—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 4:10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>833. It is practical in my opinion to bring to the attention of the
                            Foreign Office in an informal way the suggestions made in your 471, May
                            10, noon. I think it best not to try to hurry in this matter but I will
                            present it when a good opportunity is offered.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>